  "response": "Ranchi, the capital of Jharkhand, offers several interesting attractions. Here are some famous places you must see:\n\n1. Tagore Hill\n- Scenic location\n- Associated with Rabindranath Tagore\n- Beautiful views of the city\n\n2. Hundru Falls\n- Spectacular waterfall\n- Natural beauty\n- Popular picnic spot\n\n3. Rock Garden\n- Beautifully landscaped garden\n- Unique rock formations\n- Good for family outings\n\n4. Jagannath Temple\n- Beautiful religious site\n- Architectural significance\n- Important spiritual center\n\n5. Dassam Falls\n- Scenic waterfall\n- Natural beauty\n- Located near Ranchi\n\n6. Ranchi Lake\n- Artificial lake\n- Boating facilities\n- Pleasant surroundings\n\n7. Birsa Munda Park\n- Dedicated to tribal freedom fighter\n- Recreational space\n- Historical significance\n\n8. Birsa Zoological Park\n- Wildlife sanctuary\n- Various animal species\n- Educational experience\n\n9. Tribal Research Institute Museum\n- Showcases tribal culture\n- Artifacts and exhibits\n- Cultural heritage\n\n10. Ranchi Hill\n- Panoramic city views\n- Hanuman Temple\n- Peaceful environment\n\nThese attractions offer a mix of natural beauty, cultural heritage, and recreational experiences.",
